I would give Pei Wei 3.5 stars if I could.
The service was friendly and the dining area is clean and comfortable.
I had a cup of hot & sour soup, 2 wontons, 2 pot stickers and sesame chicken on brown rice.
The soup was pretty good, not great.
I would order a cup again but it's not good enough for a bowl.
The crab wontons were surprisingly tasty, next time order more.
The sauce was good as well.
The pot stickers were terrible, I would rate them a zero.
They're deep fried vs pan fried, so overcooked they were crunchy and hard.
And the sauce was awful as well.
The sesame chicken was pretty good, it has a nice fresh flavor and respectable amount of heat.
Overall I am satisfied with meal.

